#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:2 4043fcd7431e414d8cfd3005d30eef57
msgid "Wave Equation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:4 eba1edd1cf954021860645fc684be257
msgid ""
"A single script, ``examples/wave/wave.py``, solves the linear scalar wave"
" equation on the unit square with explicit central-difference time "
"stepping. It is the canonical hyperbolic counterpart to the heat example "
"in :doc:`diffusion`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:9 54d6a21e2d5849bbbede25d7411980f5
msgid "The strong form is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:11 85c6c7ee88bc400aa64f184b8097cdca
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"u_{tt} \\;=\\; c^2\\, \\Delta u\n"
"\\quad \\text{in } \\Omega,\n"
"\\qquad u = 0 \\text{ on } \\partial\\Omega,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:17 293ea772b95c4463ad87ec0f17359df8
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"with a multi-frequency Fourier-series initial condition from "
":class:`~tensormesh.dataset.WaveMultiFrequency` and zero initial "
"velocity. The script runs at :math:`c = 2.0`, :math:`\\Delta t = "
"10^{-3}`, for 100 steps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:24 611a9e4c6e3940cf90f17ab79b61d80b
msgid "Central-difference time stepping"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:26 720a7bd5ed0d46d7a78a06eaa04714f2
msgid "The standard discretization in time is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:28 b45a3f0f40d4422f8a0555f915e439ef
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"M\\, U^{n+1}\n"
"\\;=\\;\n"
"2\\, M\\, U^{n} - M\\, U^{n-1} - \\Delta t^2\\, c^2\\, A\\, U^{n},"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:34 c7c7d1a422cf4865a75f5c3c1aed5160
msgid ""
"where :math:`M` is the mass matrix and :math:`A` is the Laplace "
"stiffness. This is **explicit** in time — at each step we solve against a"
" fixed mass matrix only, so factorize-once / back-sub-many is the right "
"pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:39 f76b17c9c98e467f822f69d8531b4aea
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The first step needs special treatment because :math:`U^{-1}` is unknown;"
" using the Taylor expansion :math:`U^{-1} \\approx U^{0} - \\Delta t\\, "
"V^{0}` and the initial condition :math:`V^{0} = 0` gives"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:44 3589e6cfbf534163a01238e86419cd39
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"2\\, M\\, U^{1}\n"
"\\;=\\;\n"
"2\\, M\\, U^{0} - \\Delta t^2\\, c^2\\, A\\, U^{0}."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:52 388a47eeb61947cdbc184d7d9a89e6ed
msgid "TensorMesh setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:54 15cdba02914b465497b0ae1933ad16a1
msgid ""
"Two tiny assemblers (one for :math:`M`, one for :math:`A`), one "
":class:`~tensormesh.Condenser` for the homogeneous Dirichlet BC, and a "
"15-line time loop. Note the small helper that scales a "
":class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix` while keeping the "
"``SparseMatrix`` type:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:60 50f31651540d471d90fad5da599ba6a2
msgid "examples/wave/wave.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:97 952764026fd549ae91b836f6cbd5ee9b
msgid "A few practical notes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:99 41490c6b237c41f98b0903f5a054c8c4
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"**Stability.** Central differences are conditionally stable — "
":math:`\\Delta t \\lesssim h / c`. The script's choice (:math:`\\Delta t "
"= 10^{-3}`, :math:`h = 0.01`, :math:`c = 2`) satisfies this comfortably."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:103 6ab26acd6de444819ed379024b0831af
msgid ""
"**Factorize once.** ``M_`` (the condensed mass matrix) is recovered from "
"the first-step matrix and reused in every loop iteration; only the RHS "
"changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:106 ea9ab496e782435e9d48e5abfb0179ce
msgid ""
"**GPU-ready.** The script picks ``cuda`` when available and "
"``mesh.to(device)`` moves the entire mesh + buffers in one call. "
"Snapshots are moved back to CPU only at the end for visualization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:111 a065cf8010dc49d89d2bc88b0b31d7a4
msgid ""
"For a higher-order time integrator (Newmark, Runge-Kutta) drop in "
":class:`~tensormesh.ode.builtin.ExplicitRungeKutta` from "
":mod:`tensormesh.ode` — see :doc:`../user_guide/time_integration`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/wave.rst:123 2fa229e9dc164cd3953b890da9881354
msgid ""
"*Output of* ``wave.py``: *FEM prediction (left) vs analytical solution "
"(right) for a multi-frequency standing wave on the unit square. Phase and"
" amplitude track the analytical reference throughout the run; central "
"differences preserve energy as long as the CFL condition is satisfied.*"
msgstr ""

